#: ../../controlpanel.rst:143
# f5220ef022c94767ab589ce901d5d5f6
msgid "The following options are available when creating a new module:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../controlpanel.rst:145
# af1796edc726476ca99904b03a26225d
msgid "**FreeBSD Package:** click the \"Find\" button to browse the available categories and to select the package to convert into a PBI."
msgstr ""

#: ../../controlpanel.rst:147
# b7941ea896a9458fa74db73fc50b2efb
msgid "**Icon File:** by default, a generic PBI icon will be used. If the application has its own icon, use the \"Select\" button to browse to the location of the icon. When selecting a custom icon, use a 64x64 :file:`.png` file with a transparent background."
msgstr ""

#: ../../controlpanel.rst:150
# 7e93a6d576724d82a149ea9ce9e4fb87
msgid "**Quick Module:** check this box if the system is not currently connected to the Internet. Otherwise, EasyPBI does a scan of the package from the official repository in order to automatically fill in the module's information. This information can be filled in manually, as described in the next screen."
msgstr ""

#: ../../controlpanel.rst:153
# cb47d2255c244462b49c7350724e9e10
msgid "After making your selections, click \"OK\". The information for the module will appear as seen in the example in Figure 8.1c. In this example, the :file:`net-p2p/linuxdcpp` port has been selected."
msgstr ""

#: ../../controlpanel.rst:156
# 98832fe33d42488babff173079caec82
msgid "**Figure 8.1c: PBI Configuration Screen**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../controlpanel.rst:160
# ad9e1f767b1f4f558e14dfb2e38ecdf2
msgid "The \"Port/Package\" and \"Author\" fields are mandatory and should be auto-filled for you, unless you checked the \"Quick Module\" box. If the port does not supply the \"Author\" name, check the application's website to see if you can find one. Otherwise, input the email address of the port maintainer. A generic icon will be supplied for the module. You can change the default icon by clicking it."
msgstr ""

#: ../../controlpanel.rst:164
# 1f44e035fd6c4190aa6e48348bf1a209
msgid "The other items in the \"PBI Configuration\" tab are optional:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../controlpanel.rst:166
# ee0b16b4fc124ebf930fd77e91897a98
msgid "**App Type:** if this is empty, the PBI will not appear in an AppCafe® search unless \"Search all available PBI and packages\" is checked in the \"App Search\" tab. Otherwise, click the green arrow to select \"Graphical\", \"Text\", or \"Server\". The PBI will be assigned the icon for that search selection."
msgstr ""

#: ../../controlpanel.rst:169
# 0bcbcd86df4d4720a563923717fcbcbd
msgid "**Search Tags:** a comma delimited, with no spaces, list of tags. If a user types one of the tags into the search bar of AppCafe®, the PBI will be listed."
msgstr ""

#: ../../controlpanel.rst:171
# fa545ae77b4c4ab98bfa5a6bd9cfaf13
msgid "**Plugins:** if the application, such as a web browser, has associated plugins, click the \"+\" button to browse to the location of the plugin packages. These will be added to the \"Plugins\" tab for the PBI in AppCafe®."
msgstr ""

#: ../../controlpanel.rst:174
# cbc8ec704d3b4be4872bd1e1208c84d0
msgid "**Screenshots:** to include a screenshot of the application, click the \"+\" button and browse to the location of the screenshot in :file:`.jpg` or :file:`.png` format. The added screenshot(s) will appear in the \"Screenshots\" tab for the PBI in AppCafe®."
msgstr ""

#: ../../controlpanel.rst:177
# 9986d37f030440c6a6bc5a5afc7a9c4a
msgid "**Similar Apps:** if there are any other packages with similar functionality, click the \"+\" button to browse to the location of the plugin packages. These will be added to the \"Similar\" tab for the PBI in AppCafe®."
msgstr ""

#: ../../controlpanel.rst:180
# 53ed4f7bf6684cdaa1bb9d7d1ab0dbe2
msgid "**View Package Overrides:** check this box to display additional settings . By default, the PBI will be built using the default options provided by the package. Some defaults can be overridden in this section: the default PBI name, URL for the application's website, license text, summary, and description. You can also add additional packages to install with the PBI or delete a package that is typically installed with the application. Note that you typically should not need to make any of these changes."
msgstr ""

#: ../../controlpanel.rst:185
# 0e01d81a1e244954821b4177c9b764e8
msgid "changes within this screen will not be saved until you click the \"Save Configuration\" button. Be sure to save any changes before leaving this tab."
msgstr ""

#: ../../controlpanel.rst:191
# f2029ec558524c46a7c909daf442fb25
msgid "Advanced Module Configuration"
msgstr ""

#: ../../controlpanel.rst:193
# f2afc29181d744c4a4a39420946ee716
msgid "The \"XDG Shortcuts\" tab, shown in Figure 8.1d, is used to create desktop icons and menu entries so that the application can be easily started from within a desktop environment. This is important for graphical applications as it configures the primary method for interacting with the program."
msgstr ""

#: ../../controlpanel.rst:196
# 7288c025477e4116817479b00321771b
msgid "**Figure 8.1d: XDG Shortcuts Configuration**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../controlpanel.rst:200
# e41279dbbc264658bc9b5d0b8aca2873
msgid "Any entries currently configured for the module will appear in the left side of the tab. Click an existing entry to display its details on the right. You can remove a highlighted entry by clicking the \"-\" (minus sign) button, or create a new entry by clicking on the white paper button under the entry list which will clear the fields in the right frame so that you can input new values. On the right side of this tab, you can edit the currently selected entry and click the \"Save\" button to overwrite the current entry with the new settings. Alternately, click \"Add\" to copy the existing details to a new entry."
msgstr ""

#: ../../controlpanel.rst:205
# 3cdbea05552c4a86a2a2e7a64e262a0c
msgid "The \"Entry Details\" section of this tab are as follows when the \"Desktop\" button is selected:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../controlpanel.rst:207
# 8678a53cbed14d7d8241732b4f9d35d4
msgid "**Name:** this is the text that will appear for the desktop menu entry, and is usually the full name of the application."
msgstr ""

#: ../../controlpanel.rst:209
# 9d18d8c50a82491b80c57f26b3dd63f6
msgid "**Executable:** input the name of the executable to run. EasyPBI will automatically generate the PBI-specific path to the binary."
msgstr ""

#: ../../controlpanel.rst:211
# ed14b34ae62f472ca28dda5eafd57c1a
msgid "**Icon:** when using a custom icon, click \"Custom Icon Path\" and input the full path to the icon file."
msgstr ""

#: ../../controlpanel.rst:213
# 74b8fbee26ab4cfe9b48266489d9d05c
msgid "**Open in Terminal:** check this box if the application needs to be opened in an X terminal. This is useful for running some text-based programs that need to be embedded into a console for user interaction."
msgstr ""

#: ../../controlpanel.rst:216
# c8ec31212be6406a80c289fdf0ff69a7
msgid "**Make Invisible:** if checked, the entry will be hidden. This is not as useful for desktop entries but can be handy with menu entries."
msgstr ""

#: ../../controlpanel.rst:218
# 5ccaa0ad515444e58cc52aa651076e51
msgid "**Requires Root:** if checked, the user will be prompted for their password when the application starts. This is important if the program requires special users or groups to be created or an installation script needs access to the local system to make modifications."
msgstr ""

#: ../../controlpanel.rst:221
# 7d82767930fc4f849e8340da6d2a3d3e
msgid "If you click \"Menu\", two more fields will be added to the \"Entry Details\" section:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../controlpanel.rst:223
# 24c01a50a8224fcd868df32f2f8e28ef
msgid "**Category:** indicates the menu category that the entry will be placed under when listed in the desktop environment. Click the green arrow to see the available menu categories. The recommended category will have a small black arrow next to it."
msgstr ""

#: ../../controlpanel.rst:226
# 541a7fb73a4142c1a4d10f4e36b20eaa
msgid "**MIME Patterns:** used to associate a space-separated list of file types with the application. This is useful when paired with the \"Make Invisible\" option. For example, consider an application which has two binaries representing two different aspects of the program and an additional binary that asks which of the two you want to use. You could create menu entries for all three binaries, but make the two specific ones invisible and associate file types with them. This means that when a user tries to open one of those file types, it will automatically run the particular binary that uses it, rather than prompting the user for input about what to do with the file."
msgstr ""

#: ../../controlpanel.rst:232
# ed93c9c875ed4704a3d451f5ae6a34c8
msgid "If you make any changes in this tab, click the \"Save\" button to save them."
msgstr ""

#: ../../controlpanel.rst:234
# 528ca7a264324b12b6b7c327fb666aee
msgid "The \"Scripts\" tab, shown in Figure 8.1e, is used to create custom installation and removal scripts for the PBI."
msgstr ""

#: ../../controlpanel.rst:236
# 8443697be47e4a919ea646900b8f782a
msgid "**Figure 8.1e: Scripts Configuration**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../controlpanel.rst:240
# ce785ba06e26458e8b3fc3e40ef101d1
msgid "If you click on the drop-down menu, you will see a list of available script types, with an icon indicating whether or not a custom script exists in the module. Selecting a script type will activate a \"Create\" button if the script does not exist, or will display the full script in a box for editing."
msgstr ""

#: ../../controlpanel.rst:243
# 218892fc6c964e4ea575a841bbfc7a9f
msgid "The possible script types are:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../controlpanel.rst:245
# 5bc8b9e47bd34822b75ff3c6d01cd674
msgid "**post-install.sh**: script run after installation of the PBI."
msgstr ""

#: ../../controlpanel.rst:247
# 7641c3782c0646dda5e134d11122947f
msgid "**pre-remove.sh**: script run before deletion of the PBI."
msgstr ""

#: ../../controlpanel.rst:249
# fbe1179ce7854c98ab15167712ce4047
msgid "If you add or remove any scripts in this tab, click the \"Save\" button to save them."
msgstr ""

#: ../../controlpanel.rst:251
# 38014b83221c43cdbf7f8bb51fdb2b52
msgid "The \"Service Configuration\" tab, shown in Figure 8.1f, allows you to setup a remote graphical configuration interface for the application. This is generally used for services or daemons that do not have a configuration interface and lets the user perform tasks with that service such as modifying runtime configuration options or starting, stopping, and restarting the service. Any configurations will appear in the \"Configuration\" tab of AppCafe®."
msgstr ""

#: ../../controlpanel.rst:255
# 1274b64da10c415da1f2282c40f7a39d
msgid "**Figure 8.1f: Service Configuration**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../controlpanel.rst:259
# f0879ef9a56a4538934ed8852382deaf
msgid "The \"Visual Options\" list is used to setup the options for controlling the service. To add an entry to this list, click \"New Option\" which will open the screen shown in Figure 8.1g."
msgstr ""

#: ../../controlpanel.rst:262
# 4320ebac886e4829942df00bbd73df58
msgid "**Figure 8.1g: Adding a Visual Option**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../controlpanel.rst:266
# d187a6c95caf4b68a5c02dec3e8f0c48
msgid "Several fields are available when adding a visual option. Examples for values to use in these fields can be found in the `service configuration file for irc/bitlbee <https://github.com/pcbsd/pcbsd/blob/master/pbi-modules/irc/bitlbee/service-config.json>`_. A screenshot of the \"Configuration\" tab for Bitlbee can be seen in Figure 8.1h."
msgstr ""

#: ../../controlpanel.rst:270
# d7a0b5de8f8148c8af0c9321c08332dc
msgid "**Figure 8.1h: Example Configuration Tab**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../controlpanel.rst:274
# d39f20c00d6d4d9ab70ca46ff07def0b
msgid "The following fields are available when adding a visual option. Example values can be found in the `README-service-configfile. <https://github.com/pcbsd/pcbsd/blob/master/src-webui/appweb/README-service-configfile>`_."
msgstr ""

#: ../../controlpanel.rst:277
# 9762c6269ab3498db80b093ad4356371
msgid "**Key:** the option to set."
msgstr ""

#: ../../controlpanel.rst:279
# e33c66e3290e4a6e97b31bab8faaf8ab
msgid "**Default Value:** the default value for the option."
msgstr ""

#: ../../controlpanel.rst:281
# 8f52c52c570a41f48a0a54ae517d5bb4
msgid "**Option Type:** supported types are *ComboBox*, *NumberBox*, or *TextBox*."
msgstr ""

#: ../../controlpanel.rst:283
# a32fe82a9b8c49aea99542eb2f16c366
msgid "**Name:** the name that will appear."
msgstr ""

#: ../../controlpanel.rst:285
# 9b0314d0a2624a39bebf3151639af285
msgid "**Description:** the description that will appear."
msgstr ""

#: ../../controlpanel.rst:287
# bdde51de3a2d4799bf432b832b61188c
msgid "**Options List:** appears when the *ComboBox* \"Option Type\" is selected. Use the \"+\" and \"-\" buttons to add or remove options to appear in the list and the up and down arrow buttons to order the items in the list."
msgstr ""

#: ../../controlpanel.rst:290
# 2c81a34c947e45fcb13fc16630a728f3
msgid "**Number Limits:** appears when the *NumberBox* \"Option Type\" is selected. Set the \"Maximum\" and \"Minimum\" numbers for the selection, where the default of *0* is unlimited."
msgstr ""

#: ../../controlpanel.rst:293
# 0cd503c677874376bd346522d2aa2842
msgid "**Text Options:** appears when the *TextBox* \"Option Type\" is selected. Set the \"Max Length\" of allowed user input, where the default of *0* is unlimited. If the text should be hidden, for example when the user is inputting a password, check the box \"Hide Text\"."
msgstr ""

#: ../../controlpanel.rst:296
# 8f3a3bd3976e4dff9f966011df61f586
msgid "If you create a new visual option, click the \"Configuration Scripts\" button as these are required for the service management configuration to work properly. Three configuration scripts are required:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../controlpanel.rst:299
# 3f92aecab513485a8449e137e22c4753
msgid "**getconfig.sh:** script for retrieving the current value for a given \"Key\" from the service configuration."
msgstr ""

#: ../../controlpanel.rst:301
# 4dc7c529b27740619a304e6518b18c65
msgid "**setconfig.sh:** script for changing a configuration value for the service."
msgstr ""

#: ../../controlpanel.rst:303
# 0c657fcae9a1430287b6fcaa249456cb
msgid "**doneconfig.sh:** script that is run after changing configuration values. Usually used for starting or restarting the service."
msgstr ""

