msgid "When the disk is first attached, it will be formatted with ZFS and configured to mirror the size of the existing disk. GRUB will also be stamped on the new disk, making it bootable should another drive in the array go bad. You can add multiple disks to the pool in this manner, giving any level of redundancy that you require."
msgstr ""

#: ../../controlpanel.rst:3195
# a3a531b3c2f14187b8286d952c60d264
